Class IDMap

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap

          org.ensembl.util.IDMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map, java.io.Serializable
public class IDMap
extends java.util.HashMap

A fast hash map providing internalID -> Persistent object mapping. This class is not thread safe.

IDMap

public IDMap(java.util.List values)
Adds all the persistent objects in the list using their internalIDs as the keys. Implementation uses values.get(i) to access the list items. If it is more efficient to to access the list using an iterator consider using IDMap(Iterator) instead.

Parameters:
values - list of Persistent objects to be stored.
Throws:
java.lang.ClassCastException - if anything other Persistent objects are in the list.
